  "chapter": {
    "number": 8,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Bildad: Job Should Repent"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then Bildad the Shuhite replied:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“How long will you go on saying such things?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "The words of your mouth are a blustering wind.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Does God pervert justice?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Does the Almighty pervert what is right?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When your children sinned against Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He gave them over to their rebellion.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But if you would earnestly seek God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and ask the Almighty for mercy,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "if you are pure and upright,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "even now He will rouse Himself on your behalf",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and restore your righteous estate.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though your beginnings were modest,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your latter days will flourish.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Please inquire of past generations",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and consider the discoveries of their fathers.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For we were born yesterday and know nothing;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "our days on earth are but a shadow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Will they not teach you and tell you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and speak from their understanding?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Does papyrus grow where there is no marsh?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Do reeds flourish without water?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "While the shoots are still uncut,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they dry up quicker than grass.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Such is the destiny of all who forget God;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so the hope of the godless will perish.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His confidence is fragile;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his security is in a spider’s web.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He leans on his web, but it gives way;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he holds fast, but it does not endure.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He is a well-watered plant in the sunshine,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "spreading its shoots over the garden.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His roots wrap around the rock heap;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he looks for a home among the stones.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If he is uprooted from his place,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it will disown him, saying, ‘I never saw you.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely this is the joy of his way;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet others will spring from the dust.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, God does not reject the blameless,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor will He strengthen the hand of evildoers.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will yet fill your mouth with laughter,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your lips with a shout of joy.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your enemies will be clothed in shame,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the tent of the wicked will be no more.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
